The vast majority of malignant hyperthermia cases occur during or immediately following anesthesia. However, there is growing evidence that some patients may develop malignant hyperthermia with exercise and/or exposure to hot environments (after heat stroke).[7545]<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.mhaus.org/healthcare-professionals/mhaus-recommendations/adverse-effects-of-heat-and-exercise-in-relation-to-mh-susceptibility" target="_blank">Click here</a> to access additional information related to this topic compiled by the Malignant Hyperthermia Association of America.&nbsp;
